byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Nick Cumming-Bruce from Geneva; Palko Karasz from Budapest; Mari-Leena Kuosa from Helsinki, Finland; Matthew Brunwasser from Belgrade, Serbia; Joseph Orovic from Zadar, Croatia; and Barbara Surk from Vienna.

abstract: United Nations officials warn influx of Syrian refugees into Europe is unlikely to stop in near future and raises possibility that conditions in Iraq will force displaced people there to follow suit.
lead_paragraph: As officials warned that conditions in Iraq could send waves of displaced people to Europe, anti-migrant demonstrations erupted in Finland.

headline.main: No End in Sight to Tide of Migrants Entering Europe, U.N. Says
